

     
      WASHINGTON (June 11) -- Mustering its most magnificent tributes for America's 40th president, the nation bid a final farewell to Ronald Reagan on Friday in a funeral praising the former president for his lifelong optimism and certainty about America and its place in the world. With his sunset burial, said President Bush, ''a great American story will close.''  By NANCY BENAC, AP AOL NEWS
     
    
